Anonymous Sun 14 Jan 2024 04:54:29 No.62567975 Report
Quoted By: >>62568045 >>62568067 >>62568213 >>62568254 >>62568259 >>62568990 >>62569780 >>62573772 >>62574362
>>62566697
So yeah, that's the thing. I found this super old Rescue Rangers fan website that was evidently put up around 1999 or earlier by a guy called Paltiel Goldstein that served the purpose of introducing the cartoon's cast and hosting unofficial media, as fansites tend to do.

Here's where it gets interesting: this Goldstein guy was a total Gadget fanatic, featuring a totally separate repository link under his main page's Internet Archives tab exclusively for all kinds of original content related to her ranging from fanart to fanfictions and even personally-made rips from her episodes and converted to .gif format... all made using the equivalent of a 35-year old Amiga home computer. Being that this is the 90's, everything is provided in link format, but around ~95% of the links are broken except for a select few digital and scanned drawings from other furries, and all of the fanfictions which were smartly hosted as plain text. The site even features its own cute proprietary error handler complete with a sound clip taken from the show. Among the long list of unfamiliar artist credits, one Doug Winger stood out, and as if by divine intervention, his drawing was one of the few that managed to survive the digital annals.

I also referenced /co/'s archives in the event that this was already common knowledge and shockingly, the last time this was posted anywhere relevant on 4chan was over 10 years ago; so old Desuarchive's servers must've dumped it around the turn of the decade. Pretty impressive stuff. Now go terrify a new generation of /co/goers with this 25+ year old drawing.

https://anterras.net/CDRR/gadget_archive.html
